Interview Questions
1. What are the types of variables in Java (local, instance, static)? What access modifiers can be applied to
each, and what is the default access modifier for instance variables?
-->Types of Variables in Java
    🔹 Types:
    Local Variable
    Instance Variable
    Static Variable
    🔹 Access Modifiers Allowed:
    | Variable Type | Allowed Modifiers                   | Default Access                |
    | ------------- | ----------------------------------- | ----------------------------- |
    | Local         | ❌ None                              | ❌ Not applicable              |
    | Instance      | public, private, protected, default | **default (package-private)** |
    | Static        | public, private, protected, default | **default (package-private)** |

    👉 Important:
    Local variables cannot have access modifiers
    Instance variables default → package-private



2. What’s the difference between local, instance, and static variables in terms of scope, lifetime, and
storage? Can local variables have access modifiers? Why or why not?
-->
| Feature   | Local Variable      | Instance Variable | Static Variable  |
| --------- | ------------------- | ----------------- | ---------------- |
| Scope     | Inside method/block | Entire object     | Entire class     |
| Lifetime  | Method execution    | Object lifetime   | Program lifetime |
| Storage   | Stack               | Heap              | Method Area      |
| Modifiers | ❌ Not allowed       | ✅ Allowed         | ✅ Allowed        |

    🔹 Why local variables don’t have access modifiers?
    Because they exist only inside a method, so access control is meaningless.



